    <stitle>STARTING MOTORS - SOLENOID CHECKS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SOLENOID CHECKS</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>A basic three-terminal solenoid circuit is shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803614">Figure 14</hotlnk>and a four-terminal circuit in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803615">Figure 15</hotlnk>. With other leads disconnected, the solenoid windings can
                be checked by making the test connections covered below.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0803614" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803614" filename="../figg08/G0803614.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Solenoid Circuit (Hold-in Winding Grounded Internally)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOLD-IN WINDING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PULL-IN WINDING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. START SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BATTERY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0803615" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803615" filename="../figg08/G0803615.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Solenoid Circuit with Ground Return Terminals.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HOLD-IN WINDING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PULL-IN WINDING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. START SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BATTERY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Also refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08036_3.xml" xrefid="f0803607">Figure 7</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803616">Figure 16</hotlnk>shows the solenoid terminal plate connections.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0803616" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803616" filename="../figg08/G0803616.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Solenoid Terminal Plates</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
